parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or near-misses, which can result in injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake fluid leaks
the brakes fail to work
the vehicle coasts through intersections or stops.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission cooling system can cause the transmission to overheat, leading to premature wear, damage, or complete failure, which can result in loss of vehicle control, accidents, or costly repairs.
symptoms: Transmission overheating
fluid leaks
slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
complete loss of transmission function
vehicle stalling or failure to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or hesitation can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or premature wear on transmission components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Transmission slipping or hesitation when shifting gears
delayed engagement of gears
vehicle stalling or failure to move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or premature wear on transmission components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
clutch pedal sticks to the floor
clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause electrical fires, stalling, and loss of vehicle control, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or fails to start

smoke or burning odors emanate from the dashboard or steering column
and the ignition switch overheats or melts.

smoke or burning odors emanate from the dashboard
